Daily menu of an obese child: no breakfast and dinner embedded
More than a third of children aged 9 to 13 have overweight problems, with overweight affecting 9% of the school population and obesity at 5%.
Obese children mostly come from families with an unhealthy lifestyle, according to current research.
It again demonstrates the importance of the environment where you grow for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as a reference.
At the table, obsessive children are fed, for example, of bottles at least twice as often as children from families with a normal weight.
For dinner, more than 19% of the obese had dined fried potatoes the day before the analysis, which is linked to the “Obesity is not a coincidence” prevention program.
In families with overweight children there is no habit of playing sports, which is applicable to most current families, where only 15% of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
A survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and involved almost 900 children in elementary education from all over the Czech Republic.
It was the second edition of the program "Obesity is not a coincidence", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and the company Unilever.
So far, more than 12,000 children from 4th to 8th grade have participated in the project.
A proper diet and enough exercise in the family are determining factors, which make the number of children with overweight and even obesity decrease notably.
"Only half of the children surveyed have responded that they have five meals daily according to the regime: breakfast, lunch, food, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," one of the results of the survey.
No breakfast, but with dinner.
Specialists warn that, in a healthy development, details are also important, which also count, such as having a fixed time for breakfast in the family.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23% of school families eat breakfast at the same time.
Most families eat breakfast alone.
But the worst was discovering that in 10% of households there is no breakfast.
Breakfast is the basis of a proper daily diet.
The study shows that in the families of obese children are consumed much more frequently insane fried potatoes.
Nearly everyone – regardless of weight – drinks daily sweets (70%).
As a rule, more than 40% of the children surveyed do sports, however, among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15%.
Create your diet
The next phase of the study made it possible for the chosen guys (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
“The food preferences of Czech children aged between 12 and 15 years, from the point of view of healthy eating, are far from ideal.”
Among his favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets.
“It’s especially alarming the popularity of sweets,” the study’s final report said.
As the main meal, the palm is taken with the pasta and followed closely by the bird meat.
Practically, children always reject legumes and the taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Change to healthy habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they are given the right information.
“In the control group of the participants in the study, who filled out the questionnaire after finishing the prevention program “Obesity is not a coincidence”, a major change was made in many cases in favour of the principles of healthy eating,” the study finds.
It calls attention, for example, to the relating to sweets, where many children would start to prefer normal, running water.
Children would also choose more frequently in the questionnaire poultry meat and fish for the main meal and would restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
