Need for Speed: The Run runs across the United States.
reviewed
A journey, in principle careless, is complicated by a series of improper negligence of a routine trip during tomorrow’s turn.
To a certain extent, it was able to meet expectations, but that serves nothing, if, in reality, nothing extraordinary was intended to be done.
The new episode, to which the title is added The Run, aroused great expectations already before its premiere.
It promised that it would give new airs to the old race saga Need for Speed and, as a result of what was shown, appears as a game that should not end up being once again an action genre without more.
We also felt curious to know how the inserted scenes would be, where the main character descends from the car and walks on his own foot.
As often happens in the NFS series, the results do not vary much from what we expected.
There are races that can be given for acceptable, but in the total calculation you lose points due to absurd failures, which have already appeared in the series for years.
In reality they cannot even be called errors, but rather the incomprehensible deception of programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are introduced to a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, he is offered to participate in an illegal race across America.
You sit at the wheel on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your mission is to get the first to New York.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than fifty races.
From this it is deduced that each race takes place by a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
Thus, one does not even remotely have the feeling that the game always offers the same thing.
Some of the environments are even pleasant to see, although the technical level of the graph is equivalent to that of previous deliveries of the series.
It is nothing of the other world.
But walking through the desert, the autumn landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
So, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that diminishes visibility.
Instead, be careful in the mountains so that you are not buried by an avalanche.
According to this, each of the races is very well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that’s enough.
For a moment, you try to advance a required number of rivals (as is normal in a classic race), then you try to win time (classic duel timed) and then you are waiting for a duel against a single opponent.
In the midst of all this sometimes appears the police, which does not do but make things even more difficult.
The main feature is landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape from someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button right at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are far fewer landscapes in the game than you could expect (in particular there are only three).
But the end result is positive, because this element does not get annoying and, in the context already mentioned, is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows the footprints of previous episodes.
That means that today it is no longer a big thing, but it cannot be said to be bad.
If you are looking for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But for a race conceived with a lot of action this style of driving is quite suitable, although we can find something better among the competition games.
So far, everything is in order.
Problems arise after a while.
Unlike the correct driving models, it is no longer the same with collisions.
From games of this type you can’t expect to recreate complicated deformations and collisions, but in fact before a hit against any object, you can’t predict how your car will react, with which not everything is in order.
It is typical that, by making a very adjusted advance or driving the car with normal traffic, there are only slight scratches, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up making uncontrolled piruettes.
Or even completely destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, no big problems arise, but it can put you in a bad mood.
Resets are programmed in such a way that, when you suffer an accident or leave the track, the game restores you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, in each race only five resets are available.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it is nothing more than a help in case something goes wrong, but it is not very reliable.
Sometimes, reset does not help, it only helps to learn the given stage of memory.
A major disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find somewhere "civil" vehicles always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or you arrive five minutes before or after.
This makes you rage especially in situations, when you see that two cars that go to the meeting in opposite directions, your opponent advances without problems, but when you arrive, you have to turn or brake.
It doesn’t matter when you arrive, because it’s programmed so that the “surprise” will always happen in front of your nose.
The opponents also have an advantage.
During the whole game you will get to places where, regardless of the moment, you will always be ahead of the same opponent in the same place.
In addition, this happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must come before you, at any cost.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars that come in front of you, so at first you can scratch the car.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that it will disappoint you immediately.
And it’s a pity, because even though the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and with action, so it’s often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it doesn’t really matter, whether the merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or the ranking in the race so that you don’t get bored, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the change of cars during races.
You have to pay attention to the gasoline supplies next to the road, because right there you have to change your car, although in the vast majority of cases it will be enough for you to have what you have.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for urban areas, American heavy cars for straight highways and exotic super sports for technical driving, for example, on curved mountain roads.
In addition to the main narrative thread, there is also a parallel thread of challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know from the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also experience points for your profile, which serves both for challenges and stories.
By reaching the upper level, the driver is opened several possibilities, starting with the car and ending with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an online Autolog feature is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and provides other community features.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
With the car you get to the metro tunnel (pass), where you start running in the dark by the roads (pass).
The speed meter marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and, suddenly, the subway convoy comes behind you and takes you forward.
In the editorial we will have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game no one even thought a little or if the authors really take us for a panda of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the overall visual effects result in most cases pleasant, sometimes even superb.
It is a pity that, in the most tense moments, the quality of the image is reduced and, sometimes, in a serious way.
This especially affects accidents where many participants are involved, when continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please the majority of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of his father and his mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for his music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore rather confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely stupid mistakes, we would have trouble claiming that The Run is the best NFS game of the last few years.
It feels like the game is not over.
Fun is guaranteed, but be prepared because mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the force of airport reflectors.
The choirs of the University of Carolina will participate in the concert "Students of Terciopelo".
The joint celebration of the International Day of Students and the anniversary of the Terciopelo Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festa Academica festival.
During the event, 20 corals from secondary and university centres will be presented.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
"The University of Carolina has a high participation in the festival."
Among the current choirs are the choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, in the festival committee is rector Václav Hampl," said the head of the organization, Jakub Čaloun.
The summit of the whole festival is the free entry for all audiences to the concert of the secondary choirs, which will be held on March 17 at 14 hours in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program features the participation of the Czech jazz artist Karel Růžička and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening will be held at the venues of the Town Hall in Vynohrady the concert "Students of Terciopelo", in which university choirs, including the choir of the Uninversidad Carolina, will participate.
The Academic Festival aims not only to dignely celebrate the International Day of Students and to remember the 22nd anniversary of the Terciopelo Revolution, but also to present coral music to the highest level and to favor collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Coral Union in collaboration with the Jan Kepler High School Institute.
All the events were supported by the mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the rector of the University of Carolina, Václav Hampl.
The festival will take place between 16 and 20 November between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to celebrative concerts, a whole series of musical events, improvised student shows and morning concerts.
Interested participants can find more information on the festival page www.festaacademica.cz
