The Brand Story:
IBM begins its second century of existence
If someone sought a term that defined IBM’s strategy with great precision, the most approximate would be “long-term”.
For the general public, IBM is the symbol of a technological revolution, a company that is perceived as current and, however, has already passed a hundred years since its foundation.
The basis of this long-time character was laid by the company’s first head, the visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He has already coined the motto that many problems in the world have a solution if people are willing to think.
Its motto "Think!" became its seal, around which it will be constructing the life of the future giant (it was also the title of an internal magazine that IBM began to publish in 1935).
Watson was also the foundation of a carefully erected corporate culture.
