So was the work of the calf that identified the body of Alfonso Cano
A lofoscopist from Cali went into history as the man who confirmed the death of Alfonso Cano.
The work of these officials is key.
On November 4, a lofoscopist from Cali’s CTI came into history as the man who confirmed the identity of the FARC’s highest chief: “Alfonso Cano,” through his fingerprints.
Of the seven lofoscopists working in the CTI section, that week the turn of "availability" was touched by Eliazar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working in the judicial investigation area for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in municipalities of Chocó, where he often had to be interned for more than five days in the jungle to get to the site where the corpses were to be identified.
In 2000 he moved to the capital of the Valley and, after taking the corresponding courses, specialized in lofoscopy, which is the study of friction skin, that is, of the palms of the hands and feet.
The week of the operative against alias Alfonso Cano, Eliazar was warned to wear minimum clothes for three days.
Something big was waiting for him.
On Friday night he left for the Cauca in a helicopter from Palmira.
He knew that he had to identify two bodies and that one of them was suspected to be from the man who directed the oldest guerrilla in the world, so they asked him to carry the decadental card of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
However, when he arrived with the research team to the site where the body was found, he did not recognize it for its physical appearance, as it was very different from what he had seen in the media.
He was without a beard, dressed like a local peasant, without glasses and much thinner.
But the footprints don’t lie.
Accompanied by a galtonian lupa, ink, a transplant and a lantern, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse with those of the card.
His eye did not fail: it was Alfonso Cano.
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was in charge of confirming to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinzón, that it was the maximum head of the FARC.
In Search of the Footprint
For a dactyloscopist of the Sijín de Cali the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos made to Eliazar González, in the press conference for the operative against "Cano", is very significant.
Many people do not know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an accurate science, without margin of error, which can become key in the resolution of crimes.
Apart from identifying bodies, lofoscopists support investigations for crimes such as theft and murder and confirm the identities of the captured people.
When captured, many criminals present fake cards or lack papers.
We take their fingerprints and look for them in the database.
The investigator said that, in a case of theft, he was touched by taking a piece of wall from a house, because in that place the thief had supported his hand to pull out a strong box full of jewelry and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not suitable surfaces to make a fingerprint, but in that case we were able to get the footprint of the whole hand and identify the offender, who had participated in different thefts," he recalled.
Footprints can also dismiss or reaffirm suspects in cases of murder.
They recently found a man dead, with bottles of alcohol around him.
By means of the investigation it was determined that a relative could be suspected of the crime and, effectively, a footprint on the bottle coincided.
Although this does not guarantee that he was the murderer, it places him on the crime scene.
A fingerprint scanner from the CTI explained that on the objects “footprints are taken with chemical or physical reagents.”
When they appear, a transplant or tape is used to lift them.
After this, the prints are sent to the Asif, which is the criminal database, or to the Registry.
“The problem is that there are still many undocumented Colombians,” the CTI expert said.
He explained that not everything is as shown in the CSI television program.
As not everything that shines is gold, not everything that is touched becomes footprint.
However, if it can be used, if the respective coating is carried out.
